Pulumi is an open source infrastructure as code tool for creating, deploying,
and managing cloud infrastructure. Pulumi works with traditional
infrastructures like VMs, networks, and databases, in addition to modern
architectures, including containers, Kubernetes clusters, and serverless
functions.

Pulumi supports multiple programming languages including Python, TypeScript,
JavaScript, Go, C#, Java, and YAML. It works with over 150 cloud providers
including AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform, and Kubernetes.

Key features:
- Infrastructure as real code (not YAML/JSON)
- Multi-cloud support
- State management
- Secret management
- Policy as code
- Testing support
